The tour begins on March 22nd and goes through April 14th. Joining us are some of our favorite artists - @lovknmusic @antoinebmusic and @johnmarkpantana - you should check out all their music! 

This will be an in-the-round evening of music from all of us, and we can’t wait for the first show.

We would absolutely love if you came out!

Heart behind the Zion Caravan Tour:

One of the most fulfilling musical experiences I’ve had was on stage at the Ryman Auditorium a few years back. It was the first half of Andrew Peterson’s Behold the Lamb of God tour, which was performed “in the round” with a bunch of other artists. After we played our song, Take This Slowly, it was time to sit down on stage while the other musicians did their thing. 
For me, the following 20-30 minutes were magic. Each artist would go up to the microphone and offer their song and craft - something labored over for so long -to an eager audience ready to listen. That audience included me, and I had the best seat in the house. 

I remember being literally four feet away from Stuart Duncan (a hero of mine - amazing fiddle player for Goat Rodeo and others), Ron Block (legendary banjo player), and Sierra Hull (maybe the best female mandolinist alive), while they played as a trio, performing licks and runs on their instruments that I could never dream of pulling off.

Artist after artist would go up to the microphone and offer their song. In that short window of time, I felt a comradery I'll never forget. The evening felt "right". Somehow, at that moment, it wasn't anybody's show. It had become everybody’s show - the audience and the artists together. That feeling is something I've always wanted more of.

Six months ago or so I thought “what if we did our own tour and brought out our artist friends to play with us in the round like we did on that tour?” Maybe I could get back to that feeling. Maybe the audience could share it too. That's where the Zion Caravan Tour was born.

I can’t wait for this tour. I want it to be special. It’s a grand experiment in a lot of ways and I hope it's just the 1.0 of future Zion Caravan Tours to come. I’d love for you to come and be a part of the first one - and of course, our fellow artists, @johnmarkpantana @antoinebmusic and @lovknmusic , who I can't wait for you to hear! 
Dates and ticket links in bio!

Ps. Thanks @andrewptersonmusic for having us out that night.

Meet the Artist #1 - @antoinebmusic 

I first met Antoine Bradford a couple of years ago on the John Mark McMillan tour we were both playing on. This was the biggest tour either of us had ever been on, and for me, it felt like being a kid in a candy store.

Playing music in a new city every day, hanging out with some pretty amazing people (one guy didn't shower for the entire tour - 15 days straight), and having the kind of convos you can only have (both ridiculous and deep) while on a bus traveling down the road at 3 am. Maybe it’s more like a college field trip than a candy store. Regardless, I quickly became friends with Antoine and he ended up being the person I hung out with most on tour. He is kind, funny, big-hearted, and loves Jesus a lot. 

In addition to being a fan of Antoine as a person, I quickly became a fan of his music. It’s soulful, lyrically deep, and instantly recognizable. He is quickly carving out his own sound and style (especially with his latest releases) and I can’t wait for you to hear him play live during the Zion Caravan Tour!

Our newest single, "Come Behold the Wondrous Mystery", is out today! 

When choosing which songs to cover for our Hymns project, there are a few questions we bring to each song: Are the lyrics rich? Does it fit well with our musical style? Do we feel something when we sing it? Something that makes us cherish God more? 

"Come Behold the Wondrous Mystery" - written by @gettymusic @matthewcboswell @michaelbleecker ker and @matt_papa - checks all of these boxes for us. We loved recording it. We hope you love listening!

Huge thanks to our team for making it all happen!

BIG ANNOUNCEMENT

Over the last few weeks, we sang songs, met new friends, and had incredible experiences over the last few weeks on the road with @antoinebmusic @lovknmusic and @johnmarkpantana 

If you went to a show, we hope you loved it as much as we did! 

When we first set had the idea for the Zion Caravan Tour, we thought it would be over by now.

But things went so well and everyone was having so much fun - we just didn’t want it to end.

So it turns out we’re actually just getting started.

We want to bring the Zion Caravan Tour to your city this FALL.

If you can help us pull this off, it will be our largest tour EVER - 30 cities! 

Do you live in one of these cities? Do you know someone in leadership at a church we could reach out to?  We want to know about it! We don’t have contacts in all of these cities, but we WANT to come to see you. 

So, we need you. But what’s new? We always have, and you’ve always come through in bigger ways than we could’ve ever expected. 

***If you can help us, head to the link in bio and let us know of the place you have in mind!***

I was standing in the kitchen almost a year ago thinking “there’s gotta be a way to tour with my friends more.” 

Then the phrase “Zion Caravan Tour” came to my mind shortly after. “Is that lame?”, I wondered. “No, that is awesome…” I thought. 

And thus began the dream that became a reality last spring for our first 14 shows. 

Touring with @johnmarkpantana @lovkn and @antoinebmusic was the most fun I’ve ever had on the road. Still can’t believe the dream became a reality and that we get to do this all over again in 28+ cities this fall!

Plus we get to hang with @markbarlow this time around on half of the tour. If you haven’t heard his music (or any of these artists’ music, you should check them out!). 

So pumped for this. There are LOTS cities on this run that we’ve never played before (looking at you, Boise!). 

It’s gonna be a blast, and I hope you get to go. Tickets in bio. Take $5 off your tickets thru the end of July with code ZION at checkout!

What is the heart behind the Zion Caravan Tour?

I told this story in the spring, but one of the most fulfilling musical experiences I’ve had was on stage at the Ryman Auditorium a few years back. 

It was the first half of Andrew Peterson’s Behold the Lamb of God tour, which was performed “in the round” with a bunch of other artists. 

After we played our song, Take This Slowly, it was time to sit down on stage while the other musicians did their thing.

For me, the following 20-30 minutes were magic. Each artist would go up to the microphone and offer their song and craft to an eager audience ready to listen. That audience included me, and I had the best seat in the house.

Artist after artist would go up to the microphone and offer their song. In that short window of time, I felt a camaraderie I'll never forget. The evening felt "right". 

Somehow, in that moment, it wasn't anybody's show. It had become everybody’s show - the audience and the artists together. That feeling is something I've always wanted more of.

So I said to my friends one day, “what if our next tour was with our friends and we called it the Zion Caravan Tour?”

About five months ago that small idea became a reality when we hit the stage in Waco, TX for our first ever show. The first run of Zion Caravan shows was an absolute blast - seriously the most fun I’ve ever had on tour. 

It was everything I hoped for, and we’re working hard to make sure these fall shows are even better! 

If we’re coming thru your city, I’d love for you to come and be a part of it, along with our amazing lineup of artists, including @antoinebmusic @lovknmusic @johnmarkpantana and @markbarlow

Buckle up! Here is my quick intro to all of the artists joining us on the Zion Caravan Tour. First up! 

ANTOINE - @antoinebmusic 

I first met Antoine Bradford a couple of years ago on the John Mark McMillan tour we were both playing on. This was the biggest tour either of us had ever been on, and for me, it felt like being a kid in a candy store.

I quickly became friends with Antoine and he ended up being the person I hung out with most on tour. He is kind, funny, big-hearted, and loves Jesus a lot. 

In addition to being a fan of Antoine as a person, I quickly became a fan of his music. It’s soulful, lyrically deep, and instantly recognizable. 

LOVKN - @lovknmusic 

I'm a huge fan of Lovkn (aka Steven Lufkin). 

Steven is a cross between super hard-working, deep, goofy, sneaky, and incredibly chill. He’s absolutely hilarious (in the most random and awkward ways).  He’s also the artist that I’ve toured with the most over the years.

I keep asking him to come back out on the road with us because of the infectious positive energy he brings to any room he walks into.

He is also a true songsmith, a prolific writer, and a captivating live performer. Pumped to have him out again.

JOHN MARK PANTANA - @johnmarkpantana 

I first met John Mark Pantana at rehearsals for the Zion Caravan Tour last spring and we became fast friends. Absolutely hilarious, kind, big-hearted, super-talented. 

I love his music as well. There's nothing contrived about it. it feels like a pure extension of himself. It's what music sounds like before you start trying to make it "work" - and, to me, that’s one of the things about it that works.

MARK BARLOW - @markbarlow 

We haven’t gotten a chance to hang out in person, but I’m a big fan already just from our FaceTime calls. Potentially the goofiest out of all of us (time will tell), I can’t wait to hang out and hear him play live. His music is excellent - go check him out if you haven’t already! 

SUMMARY 

You're gonna love getting to listen to all of these guys throughout the evening! If you haven’t gotten your tickets, what are you waiting for?! You’ll likely never see this lineup all in this same room again. Go grab your tickets!

Have I secretly wished (many many times) to be led through some magical door labeled “The Indie-artist struggle is over. Let the creativity begin…”? For sure. 

We’ve at never really fit into any kind of popular Christian music scene. 

I used to kick against that reality, but the longer I’ve been doing this, the more thankful I am that we haven’t been shown through that magical, elusive door (I’m not so sure it exists anyway).

The struggle has been real, but all along the way there’s always been you guys. You are the whole reason why we’re able to make this happen. 

Showing up to our shows tour after tour and spreading the word about our music is what allows us to be able to do this on our own. Without you, there would be no music, no tours, no real chance at making this work. 

I absolutely love that every artist on the Zion Caravan Tour is independent. We’re all fighting every day to make it work. 

And slowly, each of us has been getting more and more generous support from places like Spotify, Apple Music, and Amazon Music.

I hope you come to experience one of the biggest collectives of Indie-Christian artists performing together in the same night this fall. We can’t wait to sing with you.

A case study in dreaming out loud to your friends…

A year ago I was in my friend’s kitchen, frustrated about how little I got to tour with my fellow artists friends. An idea struck, and I threw it out in the air… 

“What if we did this tour…and I asked my friends to go too…” 

We called it the “Zion Caravan Tour” shortly after, I invited my friends, and now almost a year later we’ve played 31 shows! 

These nights have been more than I could have hoped for in, and we’ve still got 10 more to go! (for now…)

To see this dream come to life has been a true joy, and I’m so thankful to everyone who has made it out to a show!

Also incredibly thankful for my friends @lovknmusic @antoinebmusic and @johnmarkpantana who I’ve learned so much from and gotten to share so many good memories with - and for @markbarlow for agreeing to join the crew on this last run! Can’t wait to hang!

This is the last chances to see this thing for a while if you live in the states, so come on out! Shows are selling out!

Surprise! Today we're so excited to release our hymns album in its entirety with the final addition of Joy to the World! 

Around a year ago, we released the first song, Be Thou My Vision, which was just an experiment. At the time we thought "Maybe we'll just do a few acoustic-y hymns as a fun side project." 

It ended up becoming a lot more than that, snowballing into an album that we’re really proud of and means a lot to us.

It feels fitting to call this album Come Behold the Wondrous Mystery because that song seemed to stand out among the rest during the release cycle. We also happened to like the cover art for this one more than any of the others. 

We hope you love this album, along with our new version of Joy to the World! 

HUGE shoutout to our producer on this project, @joeyliechty - it was a joy to work together and can’t wait to do more on the next album! 

Also big shoutout to @j.villegasiii for illustrating the cover art and most of the single cover art - we love how everything turned out! 

Joy to the World was mixed by @lukiefred and mastered by @everetthardin 

Trumpet was played by @jacob11boyer and cello was by @mountainmouthmusic 

Track list:

1. Come Behold The Wondrous Mystery
2. Be Thou My vision
3. My Worth is Not in What I Own
4. Come Thou Fount
5. I’ll Fly Away
6. In Christ Alone
7. O Come, O Come, Emmanuel
8. Joy to the World
